2. STREAK VISUALIZATION DESIGNS
================================================================================

2.1 DUOLINGO STREAK SYSTEM (THE GOLD STANDARD)
-------------------------------------------------
VISUAL COMPONENTS:
- Flame icon (fire emoji) with day count prominently displayed
- Flame color intensifies with longer streaks (amber -> orange -> red -> blue fire)
- Calendar view shows completed days with flames
- Streak counter visible on home screen at all times
- Animated flame that flickers/grows on milestone days

STREAK PROTECTION MECHANICS:
- Streak Freeze: equip in advance as insurance for missing a day
- Up to 2 freezes at a time
- Weekend Amulet: special protection for weekends
- Streak Repair: pay gems to restore a broken streak (premium)
- Streak Freeze reduced churn by 21% for at-risk users
- Allowing 2 freezes increased daily active learners by +0.38%

RETENTION STATS:
- 7-day streak users are 3.6x more likely to complete their course
- 7+ day streak users are 2.4x more likely to return next day
- Streaks use loss aversion (losing feels 2x worse than gaining)

KEY INSIGHT:
- Duolingo separated streak mechanics from daily goals
- Streaks became easier to maintain (reducing frustration)
- Removed barriers to genuine engagement

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- Primary streak display: animated flame/crystal/star icon + day count on home screen
- Streak tiers with visual evolution:
  * 1-6 days: small purple flame
  * 7-13 days: medium flame with gold sparks
  * 14-29 days: large flame with gold halo
  * 30-59 days: golden flame with particle effects
  * 60-99 days: platinum flame with aurora effects
  * 100+ days: legendary animated flame with custom effects per milestone
- Streak Shield: 1 free per week, additional purchasable with earned currency
- Streak Repair: available within 24 hours of breaking (costs more the longer the streak was)
- Weekend Mode: optional relaxed requirements on weekends
- Streak Society: badge for users with 30+ day streaks (social recognition)

2.2 GITHUB CONTRIBUTION HEATMAP
---------------------------------
VISUAL COMPONENTS:
- Grid of colored squares representing days of the year
- Color intensity = activity level (light green -> dark green)
- Hovering shows exact contribution count per day
- Shows patterns: weekday vs weekend, seasonal trends
- Satisfying to see a fully green year

WHAT MAKES IT ADDICTIVE:
- Pattern completion desire (want to fill in gaps)
- Social visibility (profiles show heatmaps publicly)
- Long-term progress visualization (can see months/years)
- Immediate visual feedback (todays square lights up)

FLUTTER PACKAGES:
- contribution_heatmap: high-performance, CustomRenderBox implementation
- flutter_heatmap_calendar: both traditional and calendar modes, ColorMode.opacity and ColorMode.color
- Supports tap callbacks, multi-language, customizable colors

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- Productivity Heatmap on profile/stats screen
- Use brand colors: empty = dark gray, low = deep purple, medium = medium purple, high = bright purple, exceptional = gold
- Tap any day to see task breakdown for that day
- Year in Review screen showing full-year heatmap with stats
- Optional: share heatmap as image (social proof)

2.3 SNAPCHAT STREAKS
----------------------
- Fire emoji next to friends name with day count
- Creates shared responsibility (both must send daily)
- Hourglass warning when streak is about to expire
- Social pressure keeps engagement high
- Simple but incredibly effective

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- Accountability Pairs: two users can create a shared streak
- Both must complete at least 1 task daily to maintain the pair streak
- Notification: Your streak with [Name] is about to expire! (hourglass-style urgency)
- Pair milestones: special badges for pair streaks at 7, 30, 100 days

================================================================================
3. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION
================================================================================

3.1 APPLE WATCH ACTIVITY RINGS
---------------------------------
DESIGN PRINCIPLES:
- Three concentric rings: Move (red), Exercise (green), Stand (blue)
- Rings fill clockwise as goals are met
- Overachievement shown as rings extending past full circle (>100%)
- MUST be displayed on black background (key design guideline)
- Line end casts shadow on underlying ring elements (depth illusion)
- Satisfying ring close animation when 100% reached
- Haptic feedback when ring closes

WHY IT WORKS:
- Clear, glanceable progress toward concrete goals
- Color-coded categories are instantly distinguishable
- The gap in an incomplete ring creates tension (desire to close it)
- Celebrating ring closures with animation/haptic creates dopamine hit
- Simple enough to understand in under 1 second

FLUTTER PACKAGES:
- activity_ring: Apple Watch style rings, customizable
- progress_circle: customizable circular progress

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- Daily UNJYNX Rings - 3 rings representing different productivity dimensions:
  * TASKS ring (purple): % of daily tasks completed
  * FOCUS ring (gold): total focus time vs daily goal
  * STREAKS ring (white/silver): consecutive days active
- Show on home screen as primary progress indicator
- Animated ring closure with particle burst when a ring completes
- Triple Ring celebration when all 3 close (confetti + sound + haptic)
- Weekly view: 7 mini ring sets showing the weeks progress
- Monthly ring calendar: each day shows miniature rings

3.2 XP BAR / LEVEL PROGRESSION
---------------------------------
DESIGN PRINCIPLES:
- Horizontal bar that fills from left to right
- Current level displayed, next level shown as target
- Animation speed matters: fast start + slow end feels more rewarding
- Color change or burst effect when bar fills completely
- Level-up animation should be a moment - full-screen overlay, particles, sound

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- XP bar visible on profile and occasionally on home screen
- XP bar uses gradient fill: deep purple -> bright purple -> gold at full
- Level-up sequence:
  1. Bar fills to 100% with accelerating glow
  2. Screen flashes with gold particle burst
  3. New level badge appears with animation
  4. Level title text animates in
  5. Reward preview shows what was unlocked
  6. Optional: share to social
- Micro XP bar appears briefly after each task completion showing XP gain

3.3 STRAVA SEGMENT COMPARISONS
---------------------------------
- Compare current performance against personal best
- Ghost overlay showing past performance in real-time
- Segment leaderboards for specific routes
- Visual indication of PR (personal record) pace

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- This Week vs Last Week comparison overlay
- Personal Best markers on stats (most tasks in a day, longest streak, etc.)
- PR celebrations when user beats their own records
- Ghost comparison: show grayed-out previous weeks progress alongside current week

