4. AMBIENT / FOCUS MODE UIs
================================================================================

4.1 ENDEL - AI-ADAPTIVE SOUNDSCAPES
-------------------------------------
VISUAL DESIGN:
- Minimalist, dark interface
- Abstract generative visuals that respond to sound
- Smooth, flowing animations (not jarring or distracting)
- Visuals adapt based on: circadian rhythm, weather, heart rate, time of day
- Mode selection: Focus, Relax, Sleep, Move
- Very little text/UI chrome during active sessions

4.2 BRAIN.FM - SCIENTIFIC APPROACH
------------------------------------
- Embeds amplitude modulations (10-20 per second) into music
- Minimal visual interface during playback
- Focus on the audio, not the visuals
- Scientific backing creates trust

4.3 NOISLI - MIXER APPROACH
------------------------------
- 16 ambient sounds: rain, thunder, wind, forest, ocean, coffee shop, train, white/pink/brown noise
- Individual volume sliders for each sound
- Mix-and-match to create custom soundscapes
- Save favorite mixes
- Clean, colorful interface with sound-specific icons

4.4 CALM / HEADSPACE - WELLNESS FOCUS
----------------------------------------
- Calm: nature scenes, gentle animations, breathing exercises
- Headspace: bright colors, cute character animations, playful tone
- Both use breathing circle animations (expand on inhale, contract on exhale)

AMBIENT VISUALIZATION TECHNIQUES:
- Floating orbs/particles that drift slowly
- Waveform visualizers that pulse with audio
- Gradient backgrounds that shift colors slowly
- Particle systems with physics-based movement
- Breathing circles (expand/contract on a rhythm)
- Generative abstract shapes that evolve over time

FLUTTER IMPLEMENTATION:
- CustomPainter for particle systems: create particles with random position/size/speed, draw using Canvas, animate with AnimationController
- particles_flutter package: ready-made floating particle effects
- particles_network: interactive connected particle networks
- Fragment Shaders: GPU-accelerated for large particle counts
- Typical setup: ~30 particles, random start/end positions, variable sizes and speeds

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- Focus Mode with ambient visualization:
  * Dark background (midnight purple, nearly black)
  * Floating gold particles that drift slowly upward
  * Particle count/speed reflects focus timer progress
  * Particles coalesce into a shape as focus session completes
  * Optional: subtle sound integration (rain, white noise)
- Breathing Mode for breaks:
  * Pulsing circle animation in brand colors
  * 4-7-8 breathing pattern (inhale 4s, hold 7s, exhale 8s)
  * Circle expands on inhale, holds, contracts on exhale
  * Haptic feedback on transitions
  * Apple Watch Breathe animation implementation available in Flutter
- Sound mixer:
  * 8-12 ambient sounds with individual volume sliders
  * Visual icons for each sound (animated when active)
  * Save custom mixes
  * Timer integration: mix plays during focus session
- Visual states during focus:
  * Starting: few scattered particles, dim
  * Mid-session: more particles, brighter, starting to form patterns
  * Near completion: particles forming constellation/shape, bright gold
  * Completed: burst animation, shape fully formed, celebration

