6. GHOST MODE / DO NOT DISTURB UIs
================================================================================

6.1 iOS FOCUS MODE (THE BENCHMARK)
-------------------------------------
- 83% of iOS users actively use at least one Focus Mode
- Complete custom UI per Focus Mode: lock screen, wallpaper, home screen, apps
- Profiles: Work, Do Not Disturb, Sleep, Fitness, custom
- Allowed contacts/apps per profile
- Time-based and location-based triggers
- Liquid Glass material (WWDC25): translucent, dynamic material for controls
  * Floats above content creating depth
  * Separates interactive elements from content
  * Dynamic, responds to content underneath

6.2 MINIMALIST PHONE LAUNCHERS
---------------------------------
- Moye Launcher: minimalist interface for reduced screen time
- Grayscale mode: removes color to reduce phone appeal
- App blocking during focus periods
- Simplified home screens showing only essential apps

ACTIONABLE FOR UNJYNX:
- Ghost Mode (branded DND feature):
  * Activation: swipe down from top + hold, or dedicated button in app
  * Visual transformation: entire app shifts to ultra-minimal UI
    - Background becomes near-black with faint purple nebula
    - All non-essential UI elements fade away
    - Only active task + timer visible
    - Gold accent becomes silver/muted
  * Ghost Mode widget for home screen showing status
  * Auto-responses: Im in Ghost Mode on UNJYNX. Ill respond when I emerge.
  * Channel-aware: pause specific notification channels during Ghost Mode
  * Scheduled Ghost Mode: daily recurring focus blocks
  * Emergency bypass: designated VIP contacts can break through
  * Entry animation: UI elements dissolve like smoke/particles
  * Exit animation: elements materialize back in reverse order
  * Stats: You were in Ghost Mode for 2h 15m and completed 4 tasks
- Liquid Glass inspired UI elements:
  * Translucent cards/buttons that show content beneath
  * Frosted glass effect on overlays
  * Depth-aware shadows that respond to scroll position
  * Flutter implementation: BackdropFilter + ImageFiltered widgets

